    <h3>Install with Bower</h3>
    <p>
      Use <a href="http://bower.io">Bower</a> to download bpmn-js and all dependencies for you.
    </p>

    <div>
      <pre><code class="bash"><span class="nv">$ </span>bower install bpmn-js</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      Checkout the <a href="https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js-examples/tree/master/simple-bower">simple-bower</a> example to learn more.
    </p>


    <h3>Install via npm</h3>
    <p>
      Install bpmn-js via <a href="http://npmjs.org">npm</a> to get access to the full project sources.
    </p>

    <div>
      <pre><code>npm install bpmn-js</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      <strong>Note:</strong> This requires additional build steps, i.e. bundling for the browser.
    </p>

    <p>
      Checkout the <a href="https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js-examples/tree/master/simple-commonjs">simple-commonjs</a> example to learn more.
    </p>


