    <h2 class="page-header" id="build-bpmn-js">Build the Toolkit</h2>

    <p class="lead">
      You can build the toolkit yourself to hack it and get access to all its features and extensibility points.
    </p>

    <p>
      Ensure you have <a href="http://nodejs.org">Node.js</a> installed on your machine.
    </p>

    <p>
      If you have not downloaded the projects source code already, create an empty folder an clone the project using <a href="http://www.git-scm.com/">git</a> via
    </p>

    <div>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js.git -b {{ site.bpmnjs.version }} .</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      Execute the following commands to fetch all project dependencies
    </p>

    <div>
      <pre><code>npm install -g grunt-cli
npm install
</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      Build / test the project via
    </p>

    <div>
      <pre><code>grunt</code></pre>
    </div>

    <p>
      Refer to the projects <a href="https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js">GitHub page</a> for more information.
